<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
  i18n:domain="launchpad"
>

<body>

<metal:portlets fill-slot="portlets">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-lifecycle" />
</metal:portlets>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">
  <div>
    <img alt="" src="/@@/faq" />
    <a tal:attributes="href context/fmt:url" tal:content="context/title" />
  </div>
  <div metal:use-macro="context/@@launchpad_form/form" />
</div>

<metal:help fill-slot="help">
  <p>Project owners and answer contacts can modify the FAQ details.
  </p>

  <div class="warning message">Be aware that there is currently no undo or
    versioning done on the content. So edit with care!
  </div>

  <p>The <b>title</b> should describe the problem explained in the document.
    Using a question works usually well.
  </p>

  <p>The <b>keywords</b> can be used to make the FAQ easier to find in
    searches. Note that it is not necessary to add words or variant of words
    already in the title.
  </p>

  <p>The <b>content</b> should contain a complete answer to the problem. If
    an external document already exists with the answer (like on a wiki),
    just give a short description and enter the URL to the page.
  </p>

</metal:help>

</body>
</html>
